        "creation_date": 1615901040,
        "body": "<p><code>unnest<\/code> is a postgresql function that can be called just like any other function. For example:<\/p>\n<pre><code>@Query(&quot;select function('unnest', w.groups) from Work w&quot;)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Although in the query posted by OP <code>unnest<\/code> is not needed at all. This is how it could be transformed into a valid JPQL.<\/p>\n<pre><code>@Query(&quot;select w from Work w where w.groups is null or function('in_array', :group, w.groups) = true&quot;)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Where function <code>in_array<\/code> may be defined as<\/p>\n<pre><code>public class MyPostgresqlDialect extends PostgisPG95Dialect {\n    public MyPostgresqlDialect() {\n        ...\n        registerFunction(&quot;in_array&quot;, new SQLFunctionTemplate(StandardBasicTypes.BOOLEAN, &quot;(?1 = ANY(?2))&quot;));\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
